      • queryInfoForBillingList

        public static java.sql.ResultSet queryInfoForBillingList()
                                                  throws java.lang.Exception
        I believe this is a depreciated method used for populating the billinglist from the patient table in the database, as opposed to the appointment table, in case you want to bill for an entire patient balance instead of on a per-appointment basis. It selects patient id, first name, last name, status, balance, street, city, state, and zip code from the patient table and address table, then left joins the information from the address table on patient table address ID = address table address ID No usages

        Throws:
